Now, provide the fix: The `annotateCalls` method should skip past GROUP and CAST nodes to find the actual callee before checking `isGet`. So we need to modify the code to repeatedly get the first child while it is a group or cast. The fix is minimal:

```java
private void annotateCalls(Node n) {
  Preconditions.checkState(n.isCall());

  Node first = n.getFirstChild();

  // ignore cast nodes (and parentheses)
  while (first.isCast() || first.isGroup()) {
    first = first.getFirstChild();
  }

  if (!NodeUtil.isGet(first)) {
    n.putBooleanProp(Node.FREE_CALL, true);
  }

  if (first.isName() &&
      "eval".equals(first.getString())) {
    first.putBooleanProp(Node.DIRECT_EVAL, true);
  }
}
```

Note: I assume `Node.isGroup()` exists. If not, we can check for `Token.GROUP`. But in the compiler, there is likely `Node.isGroup()`. Also, we need to handle CAST nodes as per comment.

